fields.descriptive_line: Vinyl doll representing a Caucasian woman in Welsh traditional dress; UK, 1955-75
fields.physical_description:
[doll] Moulded vinyl doll with a movable socket head and movable arms and legs, strung on rubber bands.  She represents a Caucasian woman dressed in a simplified version of traditional Welsh costume.  She has moulded and painted features, a short wig of auburn wool and sleeping dark blue eyes.  The clothing is mainly intended to be unremovable and consists of: 

A broad brimmed high crowned hat of black plastic with a frill of white lace to indicate the cap worn by earlier dolls.  The hat fastens beneath the chiin with tying strings of black ribbon.

A short flared cloak of red felt, glued at the neck.

A wrapover blouse of white imitation satin with a V neck and gathered wrist length sleeves with lace cuffs.

An ankle length skirt of black felt with an attached underskirt of white buckram.

An apron of white nylon lace.

Black shoes painted on the feet.
fields.location: Museum of Childhood, Creativity Gallery, case 8
